[01:33.82]CARDINAL WOLSEY	Peace to your highness!
[01:36.38]QUEEN KATHARINE	Your graces find me here part of a housewife,
[01:40.88]	I would be all, against the worst may happen.
[01:45.29]	What are your pleasures with me, reverend lords?
[01:49.96]CARDINAL WOLSEY	May it please you noble madam, to withdraw
[01:54.19]	Into your private chamber, we shall give you
[01:58.60]	The full cause of our coming.
[02:01.69]QUEEN KATHARINE	Speak it here:
[02:03.45]	There's nothing I have done yet, o' my conscience,
[02:08.21]	Deserves a corner: would all other women
[02:12.27]	Could speak this with as free a soul as I do!
[02:16.77]	My lords, I care not, so much I am happy
[02:20.73]	Above a number, if my actions
[02:23.82]	Were tried by every tongue, every eye saw 'em,
[02:28.23]	Envy and base opinion set against 'em,
