[02:44.37]CARDINAL WOLSEY	Tanta est erga te mentis integritas, regina
[02:48.69]	serenissima,--
[02:50.28]QUEEN KATHARINE	O, good my lord, no Latin;
[02:52.92]	I am not such a truant since my coming,
[02:56.89]	As not to know the language I have lived in:
[03:01.30]	A strange tongue makes my cause more strange,
[03:05.80]	suspicious;
[03:07.30]	Pray, speak in English: here are some will thank you,
[03:12.32]	If you speak truth, for their poor mistress' sake;
[03:17.08]	Believe me, she has had much wrong: lord cardinal,
[03:21.85]	The willing'st sin I ever yet committed
[03:25.90]	May be absolved in English.
[03:28.81]CARDINAL WOLSEY	Noble lady,
[03:30.31]	I am sorry my integrity should breed,
[03:34.10]	And service to his majesty and you,
[03:37.72]	So deep suspicion, where all faith was meant.
[03:42.13]	We come not by the way of accusation,
[03:45.92]	To taint that honour every good tongue blesses,
