[04:14.31]CARDINAL CAMPEIUS	Most honour'd madam,
[04:16.61]	My Lord of York, out of his noble nature,
[04:20.66]	Zeal and obedience he still bore your grace,
[04:25.07]	Forgetting, like a good man your late censure
[04:29.57]	Both of his truth and him, which was too far,
[04:33.98]	Offers, as I do, in a sign of peace,
[04:37.51]	His service and his counsel.
[04:40.50]QUEEN KATHARINE	[Aside]
[04:41.56]	To betray me.--
[04:43.24]	My lords, I thank you both for your good wills;
[04:47.82]	Ye speak like honest men; pray God, ye prove so!
